---
title: 3-Layer Control Architecture - Prompt Constraints, FSM Guards, Output Contracts
---
%%{init: {"theme": "base", "flowchart": {"nodeSpacing": 45, "rankSpacing": 45}}}%%
%% Diagram Type: Flowchart (flowchart TD) — 3-Layer Control Architecture (Prompt Constraints, FSM Guards, Output Contracts)
%% Legend: 🟪 Prompt Constraints (purple) | 🔴 FSM Guards (red) | 🔵 Output Contracts (blue)

flowchart TD
    classDef prompt   fill:#9C27B0,stroke:#6A1B9A,color:#fff
    classDef fsm      fill:#D32F2F,stroke:#B71C1C,color:#fff
    classDef contract fill:#1976D2,stroke:#0D47A1,color:#fff
    classDef decision fill:#F57F17,stroke:#E65100,color:#fff
    classDef success  fill:#388E3C,stroke:#1B5E20,color:#fff
    classDef process  fill:#00897B,stroke:#004D40,color:#fff

    START(["User Message In"])

    START --> ANALYSIS["ANALYSIS PHASE\nEstimate user's buying intent (high/medium/low), detect guardedness (holding back vs open), identify objection types (money, fear, logistics), and summarise the conversation state - this picture guides tone and next action.\n(functions: classify_intent(), detect_guardedness(), classify_objection(), analyze_state())"]:::process

    ANALYSIS --> LAYER1_ENTRY

    subgraph Layer1["🟪 LAYER 1 - PROMPT CONSTRAINTS (Soft)\n(Purpose: Set the conversational intent, tone, and instruction-level constraints before any words are generated)"]
        LAYER1_ENTRY["Decide if an immediate override is required (for example: the user asks for a straight answer, signals clear purchase interest, or the bot is stuck in repetition). If so, use a concise override template that replaces the normal pipeline. (function: check_prompt_override_condition())"]:::prompt

        LAYER1_CHECK{{"Override Condition?\n- Direct info request: user asks for a straight answer (stop probing)\n- Soft positive at pitch: user signals interest, fast-path to close\n- Repetitive validation: bot is stuck in filler affirmations that block progress\n- Explicit force override flag: operator/session metadata requests immediate override"}}:::decision

        OVERRIDE["Override Template — use a targeted instruction to answer directly or break a stalled loop; skips Tier 2–4"]:::prompt
        STANDARD["Standard Pipeline — continue with adaptive analysis and prompt assembly (Tiers 2–4)"]:::prompt

        TIERS["TIER 2-4 - Adaptive Analysis & Prompt Assembly\nTier 2: set emotional tone and style of response (warmth, assertiveness)\nTier 3: inject sales-tactic guidance (reframes, questions, pitch moves)\nTier 4: assemble the base response content for the current stage\n(see 04_prompt_assembly.mmd; implementation details remain secondary)"]:::prompt

        PROMPT_OUT["System Prompt Generated — a complete set of instructions for the LLM that defines role, tone, required info, and output format so downstream checks can parse and validate the reply."]:::prompt

        LAYER1_CHECK -->|Yes| OVERRIDE
        LAYER1_CHECK -->|No| STANDARD
        STANDARD --> TIERS
        TIERS --> PROMPT_OUT
        OVERRIDE --> PROMPT_OUT
    end

    PROMPT_OUT --> LLM["LLM GENERATION\nPrimary AI service (Groq / OpenRouter) produces candidate text and accompanying metadata (role, tokens, scoring) for validation."]:::process

    LLM --> RESPONSE["LLM Response\n(content, tokens, metadata)"]:::process

    %% Clarify concurrency: Layer 2 and Layer 3 evaluate the response in parallel.
    RESPONSE --> PARALLEL_NOTE["Parallel evaluation:\nLayer 2 decides whether the conversation may advance this turn (immediate readiness check).\nLayer 3 watches the bot's own output for failure patterns and, if found, sets flags that change the next turn's prompt (correction happens on the next turn)."]:::process

    PARALLEL_NOTE --> LAYER2_ENTRY
    PARALLEL_NOTE --> LAYER3_ENTRY

    subgraph Layer2["🔴 LAYER 2 - FSM GUARDS (Hard)\n(Purpose: Enforce that the bot only progresses stages when the user has signalled readiness; protects against premature pitching)"]
        LAYER2_ENTRY["Decide whether the bot has earned the right to advance the conversation stage — ensures readiness before more assertive or pitching moves. (functions: _apply_advancement(), flow_engine.get_advance_target())"]:::fsm

        GUARD1["Checks the conversation hasn't been rushed: ensures a minimum number of user turns in this stage so the user had time to respond. (thresholds are heuristics; configurable in analysis_config.yaml)"]:::fsm
        GUARD2["Checks for a required explicit signal (e.g., stated need or positive sign) in recent user messages before advancing; protects against false positives. (implementation: keyword/window filters)"]:::fsm
        SAFETY["Safety Valve - fallback to avoid getting stuck: if too many turns pass without progress the system triggers a controlled corrective action (configurable max_turns)."]:::fsm

        %% Provenance: Guard thresholds and heuristics are configuration defaults found in analysis_config.yaml.
        %% They are tunable and documented here for clarity; they are not claims of empirical performance.

        RESULT{{"All Guards Passed?\n(Do the checks permit changing stage now?)"}}:::decision

        ADVANCE["Advance to Next Stage — earned progression: the bot may use more assertive or closing tactics"]:::success
        BLOCK["Stay in Current Stage (Blocked) — gather more signals or ask clarifying questions"]:::fsm

        LAYER2_ENTRY --> GUARD1 --> GUARD2 --> SAFETY --> RESULT
        RESULT -->|"Yes — earned progression: move to next stage (allows more assertive tactics)"| ADVANCE
        RESULT -->|"No — not ready: remain and gather more signals / ask clarifying questions"| BLOCK
    end

    subgraph Layer3["🔵 LAYER 3 - OUTPUT CONTRACTS (Hard)\n(Purpose: Detect failure modes in the bot's own output and force corrective overrides next turn)"]
        LAYER3_ENTRY["Detect excessive validation phrases in recent bot replies (for example, repeating 'I understand' without progressing) — a failure mode that stalls conversation. (function: is_repetitive_validation())"]:::contract

        VALIDATION_CHECK{{"Validation: excessive pattern detected?\n(Does recent bot output indicate stalled conversation?)"}}:::decision

        TRIGGER["Override Triggered — set a flag so next turn's prompt will use a corrective template (e.g., answer directly or break the loop)"]:::contract
        NO_ISSUE["No validation issue detected — continue as normal"]:::success

        LAYER3_ENTRY --> VALIDATION_CHECK
        VALIDATION_CHECK -->|"Yes — mark for corrective override next turn"| TRIGGER
        VALIDATION_CHECK -->|"No — no corrective action needed"| NO_ISSUE
    end

    TRIGGER --> STORE_OVERRIDE["Store override flag (force_override_next_turn) in session metadata"]:::process
    NO_ISSUE --> STORE_HISTORY["Store conversation turn in history (flow_engine.add_turn())"]:::process
    ADVANCE --> STORE_HISTORY
    BLOCK --> STORE_HISTORY
    STORE_OVERRIDE --> STORE_HISTORY

    STORE_HISTORY --> END_NODE(["Chat Turn Complete\nNext turn starts with the FSM's current_stage and any stored override flags - override flags tell prompt assembly to take corrective action (answer directly, shorten, or break a loop) on the next turn"])

%% Provenance note moved into Layer2 to avoid parser token merging issues
